Story - Save the Day! 
- Bunch of super heroes trying to save the day
- 3 Angels saving humanity from Karma. Entropy shakes God -> Entropy unlocks Dream -> Dream unlocks Karma -> Karma unlocks Evil/Blasphemy?. The Turning point is a Scorned Father losing his daughter. The Father is already sadistic and hateful against humanity, the girl was his light. The Father is a (Calamity? opposite of Paragon) 
(current)
- The World is in repeated state of reincarnation starting from the Turning Point
-The Turning point is when The Scorned Father interacts with Blasphemy

Names:
-Gabriella: God is my strength
Raphaela: A feminine form of Raphael, the archangel associated with healing, itâ€™s perfect for a savior figure.
Cassiel: Known as an angel of solitude and tears, Cassiel could represent an angel with a more mysterious or introspective role.
-Leila: Meaning "night," it can symbolize an angel who guides people through darkness toward the light.
-Eliana: Meaning "God has answered," it has a gentle, divine resonance fitting for an angelic mission.
Auriel: A variation of Uriel, an angel of light, this name carries a sense of divine illumination.
Amara: Meaning "grace" or "immortal," it brings a sense of eternity and divine kindness.
Seren: Meaning "star," this celestial name can represent guidance from the heavens.
-Talia: Meaning "dew from heaven," it evokes a soft, nurturing image, fitting for a heavenly protector.
Seraphina: Derived from "seraphim," a type of angel, it evokes a sense of divine light and purity.
Celestia: Meaning "heavenly" or "of the sky," it aligns with the celestial theme.
Evangeline: Meaning "bearer of good news," it fits the theme of angels sent to save and guide.
Ariel: Known as a name of an angel and meaning "lion of God," it carries a strong yet heavenly tone.
Selaphiel: A traditional angelic name, meaning "prayer of God," it connects well with the mission of saving souls.

Ideas
- Eliana-leader-impartial
SKILLS:
  - Sanctuary - takes all damage in an area +> takes all damage in a far away area
  - Taunt - Redirect attack from a nearby unit +> 
  - Strength(Passive) - Units under her command has 10% chance to negate damage
- Layla-assassin-severe
SKILLS:
  - Overwhelm - take control of an allied unit, but leaves them with 1 hp on exit +> take control of an enemy unit, leave them with 1 hp on exit, exits on death
  - Decisiveness(Passive) - Units under her command has 10% chance to deal double damage
- Talia-archer-soft
SKILLS:
  - Stun Arrow - stun a unit 1 turn
  - Empathy(Passive) - Units under her command has 10% chance to heal nearby units when moving near them
  - Magic??

MECHANICS
- 3 Main Angels under player control cannot kill enemies
- Units fall under the Main Angels, they can kill enemies but are not under player control. The game is all about influencing and protecting them
- Paragons, units that are special (buffs?) something good happens when you save them. Calamities, units that have negative effects when you fail to save them.

WORLD COMPONENTS
MAP - region level
HUB - Upgrades and selection


Villains
- Karma - Believes its humanity's fault either way and deserves their punishment,
- Entropy - Did what he did because he always prefers a change of state.
- Cult Leader - Human that believes this is the coming of their worshipped god. Represents when humans turn to "faith" on hard times
- Blasphemy - Opposite of God which is destruction and desolation of everything.
- Dream - Entity with portion of God's powers. God's effort to communicate with mankind. Reason for the Nightmares
- God - Created everything but has no control over them. He himself acknwoledges the lack of control
- Scorned Father - The start of the current ongoing problem. A Calamity, opposite of Paragon. 
  Was already hateful towards mankind, but set aside his ideals in change of taking care of his daughter. Daughter dies and he turns into the Catalyst, a huge final boss inheriting previous bosses.

Entity Types
-Nightmare - basic enemy and also the general term for them. Holds you in place
-Twohead - Multiple laser with weird pattern. Offense variation
-Blob - Heavy enemy
-Spider - 
-Eyeball - 
-Zombie
-JellyFish
